A mother who claimed her three-year-old daughter was killed in a hit and run incident outside their Florida home has been charged with murder.

Maryann Schwartz told police her child, Yeliani, had been run over in the parking lot outside their apartment, but a medical examiner said the girl had died from blunt trauma.

Yeliani was also described as being malnourished and both she and her two-year-old brother, who is now in protective custody, were covered in bruises.

